topic.title: Pattern Generator and Monitor Command

body.p: The Pattern Generator Command provides control of the Tx Pattern Generator at the physical layer. There are four sub-commands, which are Get Pattern Generator, Set Pattern Generator, Get Pattern Monitor and Set Pattern Monitor. These sub-commands share a set of MRPC Command Return Values, as summarized in
Note that this MRPC command operates at the switch level minimum bifurcation setting. For a 100 lane device, this would be 48x2 + 4x1 = 52 ports.
For example: To enable patterns on all lanes in a x16, this MRPC needs to be called 8 times (one for each pair of lanes in the port).

topic.title: Pattern Generator and Monitor - Error Injection Sub-Command

body.p: The Error Injection sub-command is used to inject some errors to generator on a Tx port.

table.title: Pattern Generator and Monitor Command Error Injection Input Data

body.p: Specifies the Pattern Generator and Monitor Sub-Command. Set to 0x4 for the Error Injection operation.
Port ID of the Tx to inject errors.
Inject Error Count fields specify the error counts to be injected on the Tx Port.
Error can be injected on a per lane basis of a port. It can only be injected when one of the following pattern is generated on the Tx port.
There is no output data for this sub-command. The error count injected can be retrieved in pattern monitor of a Rx port.

note.p: Although the range for the error count is from 0 to 0xFFFFFFFF, it's recommended that the errors injected should be less than 1000. If error injections are greater than 1000, then firmware would run a risk of consuming too much resources, and ultimately, crashing due to a watchdog timeout.
